                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Delhi team on visit
  - Ministers meet CM, to tour Kandhamal        OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Meira Kumar, P.R. Kyndiah and Sharad Pawar in Bhubaneswar on Monday. Picture by Sanjib Mukherjee                                        
	Bhubaneswar, Nov. 17: A three-member central team, headed by Union agriculture minister Sharad Pawar, today met chief minister Naveen Patnaik to discuss the situation in Kandhamal and measures initiated by the government for confidence-building and rehabilitation of riot-hit people.        
	Naveen told the team  which also includes Union tribal affairs minister P.R. Kyndiah and social justice minister Meira Kumar  that there had been no violence in Kandhamal in the past month and more than 15,000 riot victims staying at relief camps had returned home.         
	Pawar told reporters that they had come to Orissa to assess the situation and how to help and support the state government in restoration of normalcy. Our efforts will be to see that the situation normalises, he said.        
	Pawar said they had a preliminary round of discussion with Naveen. We will have a final round of discussion on Wednesday after visiting Kandhamal to make an on-the-spot assessment of the situation tomorrow. We will also meet political parties and NGOs before winding up our visit.        
	The state government announced compensation for reconstruction of churches and temples.         
	For fully damaged churches and temples, the compensation has been fixed at Rs 2 lakh, while for partially damaged churches and temples, the amount will be Rs 1 lakh.                                                                                                                                                                          
